		<div id="comment_body_64572071"><p>Which is why certification is a thing. The principles behind ASIL certification are not that dissimilar to that used in any other high risk or hazardous industry. I've seen operator stations at chemical plants show BSODs before. I've seen engineering stations show BSODs before. You know what happened in either case?</p><p>Nothing.</p><p>The principles of redundancy and compartmentalisation of functionality are there to ensure that when the shit hits the fan your brakes and steering will continue to work just fine. That's<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

